### Background and motivation

There is an internal constructor on `CngProperty` that accepts the `value` as a `ReadOnlySpan<byte>`.

https://github.com/dotnet/runtime/blob/be20c44826bc55d201c406f4ac007d24ed7a9137/src/libraries/System.Security.Cryptography/src/System/Security/Cryptography/CngProperty.cs#L30

I propose making this public so that callers that have data as a `ReadOnlySpan<byte>` don't need to convert it to a `byte[]` first, and then get copied, again, since it keeps a defensive copy.

### API Proposal

```diff
namespace System.Security.Cryptography {
    public partial struct CngProperty {
-       internal CngProperty(string name, ReadOnlySpan<byte> value, CngPropertyOptions options);
+       public CngProperty(string name, ReadOnlySpan<byte> value, CngPropertyOptions options);
    }
}
```


### API Usage

```csharp
ReadOnlySpan<byte> value = "I need a nap"u8;
CngProperty test = new(
    "CustomLabel",
    value,
    CngPropertyOptions. CustomProperty);
```


### Alternative Designs

_No response_

### Risks

_No response_

dotnet/runtime#77541.body:
### Background and motivation

Introduce public feature flag, that could be used to decide if the application could 
- create threads 
- call blocking `.Wait()` methods on synchronization objects.

On systems that are single-threaded, those APIs throw PNSE.

There are 3rd party libraries that need different implementation for single-threaded browser. 
Because in that environment, they can't create background worker thread. They have to use async/timer instead.
Here is [relevant example](https://github.com/open-telemetry/opentelemetry-dotnet/pull/6379#discussion_r2311386226) from OTEL.

Another example is [Avalonia](https://github.com/AvaloniaUI/Avalonia/blob/d500f9112101e440f334904a232e71a0f12bafc1/src/Browser/Avalonia.Browser/WindowingPlatform.cs#L37-L53)

### API Proposal

```diff
namespace System.Runtime.CompilerServices;

public static class RuntimeFeature
{
     // Existing APIs
     public static bool IsDynamicCodeCompiled { get; }
     public static bool IsDynamicCodeSupported { get; }
+    [System.Diagnostics.CodeAnalysis.FeatureSwitchDefinitionAttribute("System.Runtime.CompilerServices.RuntimeFeature.IsMultithreadingSupported")]
+    public static bool IsMultithreadingSupported { get; }
}
```


### API Usage

We already have internal internal `Thread.IsSingleThreaded` which we use inside of `System.Private.CoreLib`

```csharp
private bool SpinWait(int millisecondsTimeout)
{
    if (IsCompleted) return true;

    if (Thread.IsSingleThreaded)
    {
        return false;
    }
    ...
```

We can get rid of conditional compilation and use this as a linker feature. For example in JavaScript interop code.

```diff
-#if FEATURE_WASM_MANAGED_THREADS
+if(!RuntimeFeature.IsSingleThreaded)
+{
    lock (ctx)
    {
        // this means that CompleteTask is called before the ToManaged(out Task? value)
        if (holder.Callback == null)
        {
            holder.CallbackReady = new ManualResetEventSlim(false);
        }
    }
+}
-#endif
```

Based on this we would also create `PlatformDetection.IsSingleThreaded` and `PlatformDetection.IsNotSingleThreaded`

```csharp
[ConditionalFact(typeof(PlatformDetection), nameof(PlatformDetection.IsNotSingleThreaded))]
{
    var e = new ManualResetEvent(false);
    ev1.Wait(); // this is unsupported API on browser and throws PNSE
}
```

### Alternative Designs


`RuntimeFeatures.IsThreadingSupported` (existing similar API: `RuntimeFeatures.IsDynamicCodeSupported`).
`RuntimeFeatures.IsSingleThreaded`
`Thread.IsThreadingSupported`
`Thread.IsSingleThreaded`
`Thread.IsThreadStartSupported`

### Risks

dotnet/runtime#99691.body:
### Description

InMemoryDirectoryInfo does not work with the ".." pattern.  DirectoryInfoWrapper, however, works as expected.  I believe the problem is that the FullName does not get normalized in the private constructor when called with normalized=true and thefore has a trailing "..".

### Reproduction Steps

```c#
/*
 * - C:\
 *     - Folder1
 *         - File1.txt
 *     - Folder2
 *         - File2.txt
 */

// Initialize
var rootDir = "C:/Folder1";
var matcher = new Matcher();
matcher.AddInclude("../Folder2/**");

// Test #1 - GOOD
var result = matcher.Execute(new DirectoryInfoWrapper(new DirectoryInfo(rootDir)));
Debug.Assert(result.HasMatches); // <== Good

// Test #2 - BAD
result = matcher.Execute(new InMemoryDirectoryInfo(rootDir, new[] { "C:/Folder1/File1.txt", "C:/Folder2/File2.txt" }));
Debug.Assert(result.HasMatches); // <== Bad
```

### Expected behavior

InMemoryDirectoryInfo should work with ".." pattern.

### Actual behavior

InMemoryDirectoryInfo  does not work with the ".." pattern.  DirectoryInfoWrapper, however, works as expected.

### Regression?

_No response_

### Known Workarounds

This is a hacky workaround I came up with.  Use at your on risk.

```c#
/// <summary>
/// The InMemoryDirectoryInfo does not handle ".." correctly because the FullName does not get normalized
/// when calling the private constructor with normalized = true. For exammple, the path looks like
/// "C:\Path1\Path2\.." when it should have been transformed into "C:\Path1".  I have reported this bug
/// here:  https://github.com/dotnet/runtime/issues/99691.
/// </summary>
internal class InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix : InMemoryDirectoryInfo
{
    private static readonly FieldInfo _filesField = typeof(InMemoryDirectoryInfo).GetField("_files", BindingFlags.Instance | BindingFlags.NonPublic)!;

    public InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix(string rootDir, IEnumerable<string>? files)
        : base(rootDir, files)
    {
    }

    private InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix(DirectoryInfoBase parentDirectory)
        : this(parentDirectory.FullName, null)
    {
        // Set here instead of passing above to avoid re-normalization of the file paths.
        _filesField.SetValue(this, _filesField.GetValue(parentDirectory));
    }

    public override DirectoryInfoBase? ParentDirectory
        => base.ParentDirectory is { } parent ? new InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix(parent) : null;

    public override IEnumerable<FileSystemInfoBase> EnumerateFileSystemInfos()
        => base.EnumerateFileSystemInfos().Select(x => x is InMemoryDirectoryInfo dir ? new InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix(dir) : x);

    public override DirectoryInfoBase GetDirectory(string path)
        => new InMemoryDirectoryInfoBugFix(base.GetDirectory(path));
}
```
### Configuration

_No response_

### Other information

_No response_

